cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on deep learning-based anomaly detection techniques. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often utilize deep learning for anomaly detection. It could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as anomaly detection is important in security applications. Finally, it may also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as deep learning is a subfield of neural computing.
